                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       New players in hospitality
          GARIMA SINGH NEOGY                          REalty dreams                                  
	New Delhi, April 14: Realtors Amrapali Group and Raheja Developers are planning to enter the hospitality segment.        
	Amrapali is planning to invest nearly Rs 1,000 crore in building three, four and five star hotels in the country.         
	It is already building hotels in Bareilly, Vrindavan, Greater Noida, Udaipur, Indore and Jaipur.        
	We are planning a pan-India expansion. The hospitality industry is booming and it is logical to venture into this growing area, Shiv Priya, executive director of Amrapali Group, told The Telegraph.        
	Amrapalis upcoming properties include budget hotels. While the group has signed management contracts for a few of its upcoming properties, negotiations are on for the rest of the projects, Priya said.        
	The group has already signed a management contract with Choice Hotels for its budget hotel in Greater Noida.         
	Raheja Developers is also planning to enter the hospitality industry in a collaboration with the Tatas Indian Hotels.         
	It plans to set up six hotels in four years. Four of the properties will be business hotels in the four and five-star category. Two will be budget hotels, said sources in Raheja Developers.         
	The company will build a 300-room, stand-alone hotel in Gurgaon at an investment of Rs 150 crore.        
	The Rahejas plan to build two business hotels in Gurgaon and Panipat.                                                                                                                                      
